Very few people really know me even less understand me. But someone I was once really close to would tell me to "practice my friend making skills" every time I went to work a few years back.  And it kinda helped.  I am shy and it's hard for me to put myself out there and have people tell me I'm not worth their time (and it has happened to me, which makes it even harder to do it sometimes) but this whole week and me being so nervous with starting at a new place and hoping beyond hope that I'll be as happy here as I was in Flagstaff, has that little piece of humorous encouragement replaying over and over in my head as I try to meet new people and my new coworkers and try and find a place I belong. I do like my job, I just hope beyond hope that I make friends here too.  So, I continue to "practice my friend making skills" and try to come out of my shell a little and make at least a good impression as a worker, and hopefully make friends eventually.

Apparently everything I thought of my life was wrong...learning that really sucks.  Who can one turn to when everyone you've ever trusted turns away?

I could become a bag lady
Maybe I'll start supporting myself by collecting cans
Maybe that can support some new habit that will help to make it all go away or at least dull it

Mental institution here I come!


Or maybe I'll just reduce myself to moving home and wallowing in my failed existence and my failed character.

Well some interesting stuff has developed lately...and I'm not quite sure how I feel about any of it, or what I'm going to do exactly.  Basically, heat is in my future...maybe 2 months, maybe 8 I don't know but it is going to be interesting for sure to see what happens. 
I've been trying to reconnect with some people from my past lately.  We haven't kept in the best contact, but we've always been there for each other and I kinda need that right now.  Contact with someone.

My parents are coming up for the 12 (exaggeration) weekend in a row, it's actually only been like 6, but this is the last one because the trailer is closed, but they're coming up for Homecoming with some other parents of students that we know and we're going to party hardy (lol) we're going to tailgate and have a lot of fun I know.  I'm kinda excited to see everyone and have fun like it should be. 

I know I'm going to be in the minority in this, but I seriously think that tequila sunrise is a bad idea.  Not necessarily the fact that the bars are going to open so early, but the fact that people aren't just going to get up early to drink.  From most people I've heard that are excited to partake this year the plan is to start drinking Friday night, drink all night, and go to the bars without sleeping at all at 6am, then passing out for a little while and getting up in time to tailgate before the game.  To me that sounds stupid and dangerous and not really that fun.

I'm not partaking this year because for one my parents will be coming up early Saturday and for two I have a 9am meeting at the RL--ohhh fun!  And I think it's stupid, I'd rather sleep at 6am than drink.  But I do plan on having fun at the tailgate and most likely later that night when the parents have gone back to Munds Park, or we've come home from Munds whatever happens. 

So, I'm kinda rambling at this point and I really should do something a little more productive, we'll see what happens...

I figured I'd say a little something real quick before my drive home.  This weekend was awesome and I couldn't have asked for a more perfect weekend with my family, or a more perfect gift to my parents to show them how much I appreciate everything they've ever done for me, including being in love for 25+ years and having a loving and stable environment for me and my brothers to grow up in.  All I can ever hope for me or anyone else I know is that they are able to have such a life with another person.  I am and forever will be inspired by the relationship of my parents.

So, the party was the bomb diggity!! My parents were shocked, a ton of people showed up, some of whom they haven't seen in years! It was awesome, everyone had a GREAT time and I'm now exhausted! everyone is. Maybe I'll update more soon, but as of tonight I'm the greatest daughter ever :) nice...

It's weird that I'm actually updating because if I've been online the past 4 months it's been briefly and pretty much to just check my email, so to actually have access to a computer with time to spare, is foreign to me at the moment. So, lets do a quick like update... This summer was a good summer, a lot of stuff happened, most of which I don't feel like getting into currently, that has helped me to define me and figure out my future plans. But I had fun, went a little wild, made some money, spent a lot of freaking money, drank a lot, worked a lot...and saw some of the people I care the most about. School's started and I'm enjoying the semester, light class, extra work, and some fun in the midst of things. I've been hit on like crazy for some reason by some interesting people. And if nothing else it's helped boost my confidence. Some people are upset at me for standing up for myself and being honest about how I feel. I can handle that. I'm tired of hiding who I am and my feelings all to make others feel okay and me feel like crap. Those aren't real friends if I have to watch everything I do in order to not make a scene. I do admit that I've made some mistakes recently...in confrontation, only in regards to one person, in not talking to people, that numbers far greater. But I honestly feel that because of my confrontation with one, everyone is upset with me, and I don't feel like I have to explain anything to anyone because it was only between 2 me and the other. Anyways...I don't even want to think about that I'm currently in Phoenix, because on Tuesday my parents celebrated their 25th wedding anniversary! That's a long time for sure by today's standards, and they don't know it but in about 6 hours just about everyone they know is going to be arriving for a surprise party. This has been so much work and planning and secret keeping. I'm so ready for it to happen already!! It's been so nerve-racking and I've spent countless hours on the phone calling people and planning and arranging and making my brother do stuff for me. I can't wait! Well, the 'rent's should be leaving soon and so I believe I'll jump into the shower so that ray and I can start shopping real quick :) I'm soo excited!! Maybe I'll get around to being online more often, but no promises :) I hope you all are well, and I hope to talk to some of you soon!

So it's 3am and I'm wide awake (because I took a nap earlier) finishing the packing because in the morning I sign the contract and move into my new apt with Wendy.  Most everything is packed and stuff, it's just the little things and last minute things.  Basically it's all getting thrown into one big box at this point because that and bags is all I really have left.  Then tomorrow and Sunday and Monday I get to clean, well clean until I'm done cleaning, and officially move out and stuff, yeah :)

Blah blah blah...my knee is wrecked again, hopefully me keeping the brace on it pretty much all day will help it to not hurt so much, either that or I'm going to have fun wrapping it until it does feel better.  

I really like Iron Chef, and Reces Pieces :) yummy!

Anyways back to the packing... and maybe another nap at some point...

I have some of the prettiest bruises on my legs right now from running into corners and dropping couches on my legs when helping Angela and Patrick move into storage.  Not to mention a semi-sore neck, back, and legs from the lifting. I'm getting so tired of this packing and stuff, (I have A LOT of books! and craft stuff, and stuff in general) I wish there were someone that could come over and keep me company and help this process go by less painfully, but alas, there's nobody I feel I can call do fulfill that request, ohh well...I guess I'll just get back to it...my packing, cleaning, and procrastinating...

Last night was so fun...the past week or so has been though, fun and crazy and busy, with not enough sleep, and too much caffeine :)

He said we'd talk later, I hope we do, but it at least has me feeling better.  I'm kinda impressed, or I will be if we actually talk.  That'd mean he's trying not to run away from confrontation anymore.  We'll see...But it makes me feel better either way. 

But last night even after the party was intense but fun.  And we'll leave it at that.  

I'm still and probably will forever remain the eternal good girl who hasn't done anything.  I think it's funny when people try to peer pressure me into things.  Dude!  If I haven't succumbed to peer pressure in the last 21 years, why would I start now?  I've made decisions in my life, things that I believe, and I refuse to be a hypocrite to myself...not because of what anyone else thinks but because I have to live with the decisions I make.  Once again peer pressure doesn't work, and if I believe something I'm not going to go against that.  So, I'll forever be the good girl who's done nothing and seen a lot.  Whatever...

I guess I'm done rambling, I need to get ready to move furniture into storage for Angela and Patrick...if anyone wants to help, come on over ;)

So, this morning, I went to the new apartment with Wendy, looked at it, decided to take it, filled out applications and figured out what I was doing for the next 13 months.  They were running a special or something like that and signing for 13 months the deposit is cut in half and first month rent is free! How sweet is that?!
Then I went to the Newman Center and finished the banner for Pentecost, made some flyers, cleaned up the blue dell's desktop, did some other stuff...I don't remember right now.  I ordered shoes for my new job :)
Then Jordan arrived and we chatted, I finished up some stuff, then we went and saw her cousin's husband's sister in the track meet at NAU it was some big finals thing, montana, eastern washington, portland...some other schools were competing and stuff, it was kinda cool, plus there was a really cute little boy in the group next to us who kept running around and jumping and trying to be a long jumper, it was so adorable!
Then we went to dinner (yummy!) and Kate McCarthy and her date Brian came and joined us for a little bit and we talked and caught up and had a great time.
Then we went to the bars for a little bit, but we didn't really know anyone there and they weren't playing good music, so we ended up at Colin's Pub, played a game of pool and got hit on by this old guy who didn't speak English.  I've come to realize that the only guys who ever hit on me are either considerably older or considerably younger than me and don't speak English.  So, if I'm ever going to find someone I better enroll in a Spanish class. Whatever.  
Then we left and went to Walmart and Jack in the Box.
Then made a graduation gift for a friend and now I'm exhausted and tomorrow is another long day (or today I guess)

Jordan graduates at 10, there's a reception BBQ thing afterwards, then I'm going to try to get down to Prescott before Dan leaves and see him and Jes for her graduation.

Sunday Pentecost service is at 11am in THE DOME ;P I have to be there at 9:30 to get stuff ready and then I get to help clean up afterwards, and there's a potluck at Pius afterwards and then I told Michael I'd work at the Newman Center on Sunday too.  

So basically it's a long and fully and hopefully fun weekend :)  Then Monday starts my new job!!

Yeah, well, it's 2:30am and I'm so tired and I have to be up for graduation soon, so goodnight all I hope you're doing good!!

Seriously...I've had like the greatest week, not only have the past few weeks been relatively stress free with me getting my papers done and knowing final's would be pretty easy, making me happier than I have been in a long time.  On Monday, I talked to Wendy and we decided to live together, taking the living situation for the summer and next year totally off of the to do list, plus it's Wendy, so that's going to be fun anyways! Then I finished finals today, and I was offically hired at Red Lobster today too...I go in tomorrow to fill all the paperwork out and stuff.  So, it's exciting and everything is coming together, and I'm still in a fabulous mood which is so good because I've missed that. As I'm sure those around me have too. 
So, tomorrow, I fill out paper work for my new job :) work at Michael's, do truck, get utterly exhausted, then go and hang out with my friends and have fun!!  Sounds like an almost perfect day (it'd be perfect without the getting exhausted from truck part, but ohh well).  

Life is good, my parents may come up this weekend, if not, I'm going home Wednesday because Ray graduates on Thursday!! Insane isn't it!  

Smiles all around for everyone!  Nothing could make me happier at this point, or bring me down I believe and if I believe it, it is true (or something like that ;P)

I'm bored...catch you on the flip side 

(ohh yeah!! another fun thing, dan totally fixed my computer and it's fast now, not slow and dumb, it's great!! He's the bestest!)

Night!!
I feel like I'm losing all my friends.  It makes me sad, and lonely...

This story was in the social work group and I think it's awesome!  We should all do it, I think: Paperclip

All in all it was a good weekend for me.  I relaxed, worked, saw my family, had fun, went to Church...nothing out of the ordinary, but good none the less.  (I was in a really good mood at Church, I kinda scared a few people haha, they're not used to seeing me happy or something like that)

I'm really excited about this Bread for the World letter writing campaign.  I hope people participate and we get a lot of letters so that we can hopefully convince congress to keep their promises and help to end hunger in the United States and then the world.  Social Justice stuff really gets me happy and hopeful.  A few people seemed really interested, and for those of you who may be interested but don't come to the Newman Center, we still need your help, just ask and I'll tell you all about it, in fact I may just post something tomorrow anyways.  But help, it's worth it and so simple...a letter, and I have sample letters so it doesn't take much thought or time. If you're not going to stand up and try to make the world a better place, who are you expecting to? (I guess I'll jump off my soapbox now)

Anyway...I'm thinking of doing dinner around 6:30 on Friday.  I hope this works for most of you, and I think it will.  But let me know if it does or doesn't and we'll try to find a better time for everyone.  

But yeah, bed time :)  Have a good night everyone, and a good reading week!  This is the last week before finals, I'm ready to be done for sure!

Sleep well!

My family was in town today :)  Ray came up early with a friend and he bought me lunch, and then I had dinner with them and my parents..yeah!  Tomorrow I get to drive down to Munds Park for lunch and my dad's going to make me food...I love it when the parents/family comes to visit :)

So, I'm losing my voice :( and I have a sunburn from building a fence this morning.  So, tonight after work I went and I got assorted Tazo tea :) and aloe vera for my burn...so I'm sore, tired, and happy...yay!

So, off to drink my calming tea and and reapply aloe until it doesn't burn anymore 

Goodnight y'all ;)

So, today, was another day I guess.  

I'm starting to get sick I can feel it, I have a headache and my throats starting to get rough and stuff. But other than that it was a good day. 

I had class, came home to shower and eat, ended up eating and falling asleep for like 5 hours, woke up, cleaned up a little, went to the Newman Center for EXALT, which was really good actually.  There were a lot of people there and I knew most of them which was awesome.  The music was great and Fr. Billy gave a great teaching on the 7 gifts of the Holy Spirit. I always kinda knew what they were, but it makes so much more sense now. He used a mountain as a visual and it kept reminding me of the book Hinds Feet on High Places which was cool, because that's like one of my favorite books!  But it was just all so much more clear, which was awesome! I also got to see my confirmanii and other teens I haven't seen in a while and my peers too, I love knowing people :)

After EXALT I hurried my butt over to Wilson because I was late, I was supposed to be there at 8:30, EXALT wasn't even over until 8:45...ohh well, I made it in time to eat and socialize with my friends.  We had a great time, we always do though, so yeah, it was great.  After pizza we went to Barnes and Noble for dessert (with 2 s's :P) because Beale was working and couldn't join us for pizza, so we got stuff 1/2 off, sweet (!!) and laughed our butts off and continued our good time. We found this book about "REAL NINJAS" and we were reading from that.  And Aub's and I decided that if one of the requirements in the book was that you had a penis, we'd be ninja's according to the rest of the requirements, except for the ultimate test, keep those frozen baby carrots away from us!! :)  We also got kicked out of Barnes and Noble because we were there past close...oops, ohh well.  I don't think they would've said anything if there weren't five of us making a lot of noise, but we were and it was time to go.  

So, now I'm home again, about to start reading probably, listening to my ceiling leak as it hits the bowl I put under it because the pitcher wasn't wide enough because there's 2 leaks now, I really need to get down to the office and report it because it's getting annoying and I can't get to the bathroom without getting dripped on...blah!

I've been updating a lot lately, some of it is relevent to my life, on a personal like level (well mostly my day and fun stuff that happened, which I've been missing), other is stuff relating to the pope mostly.  I'm really excited about this new pope, I'ma little leary of some stuff I've heard, but at the same time, we have to give him a chance to actually be pope before anyone passes judgement.  He was obviously the man that's supposed to be Pope otherwise he wouldn't be...100+ men of the cloth thought he was being called to lead us.  We have to trust that God had a hand in that decision, and I believe He did, and I intend to trust that He knows what He's doing, and that it's right for the world :)  Now I'm done with that.  I'm excited to see what happens, this has got to be an insane time for him (B4squared) and I hope he has the energy to keep up especially these first few weeks (he is 78 for goodness sake).  Just say a little prayer for the pope.

Ohh yeah, and say a little prayer for Jason and Sarah Kidd too...I didn't actually hear if the test went the way they want it to, but hopefully it does because they want it and they deserve it, and it would be so exciting I think! (If you're curious ask me, but I'm not going to post it all over the internet, because it's not my news and I don't have all the information).

Anyways, I'm off to either read or shower, I haven't quite decided, both will happen tonight it's just the order that's in question at the moment.  Call me if you want, I'll be up, not only did I take a nap (unintentionally) I had chai tea (which has caffine) so I'll be up for a while.  

I hope you're all well, and I'll talk to you soon, if I haven't already :)

So watch, the next t-shirt or flyer Jason makes with Benedict XVI on it will say B4squared..lol.

After dinner I went to Charly's and hung out with Gabriela and her friends and listend to a bunch of people play open mic...Charly's is pretty chill Tuesday nights...a pretty artsy crowd thought I guess.  Gabriela didn't play until midnight, so we were all exhausted by then, but we kept ourselves entertained I guess. Gabriela and her friend Nate picked each others noses.  Gabriela's other friend Shannon, lifted the pant leg of a guy walking by to check and see if he was really wearing black socks with tennis shoes.  They all drank, we listened to good music, and some weird music...what did they call it, not music, it was impressionistic art or something like that, it was weird let me tell you that. So, all in all, yesterday was a great day :)

What does today hold?  I'm not sure, but we might get together for pizza after EXALT.  Let me know if that's changed at all by the way...

Ohh yeah, if anyone orders pizza today, make sure it's from Pappa John's and mention Best Buddies and they get some percentage (20%)of all the pizza order or something like that.  I suck at remembering...so that might be what needs to be done, I know it's Pappa Johns and I know it's Best Buddies...that's all I guess :)

Anyways, have a great day y'all and I hope to see/talk to you all sometime soon.

I'm not who I want to be right now...I know this...I'm not even sure who I want to be, I just know this isn't it.

Tonight was really great actually, especially seeing how I went to the Newman Center.  That place is a looming omen of doom to me most of the time and it was when I got there today, but I got a free dinner, and the speakers were amazing, they really rejuvinated my soul I guess. 

My goal in life is to be a Social Worker, to be involved in social justice and serve others and the community.  My goal at the Newman Center is the same thing. However, being the intern with the stresses and responsibilities and frustrations, I haven't had ANY opportunity to really go after that.  And in school it's always learning and writing and learning, not doing...I'm just burnt out in my life it seems, as my previous entry obviously conveyed. And to see people living the way I want to when I'm done here, just gives me so much hope that there is an end to my current frustrations and even though I have no time right now in four weeks, I am free to start doing real service and real soul searching and real spiritual diving for myself.  It gives me the needed strength to make it through the next four weeks so that I can do what I'm longing to do. 

I told everyone basically that I'm not going to be an officer for the Newman Club next year, but I am willing to take on service...I'm willing to make sure that the Newman Center offers opportunities to help our community as much as possible.  This is what I want to do, this is part of what I'm supposed to do, and by only answering to me and not Colleen and Michael I'll have more motivation and more freedom to work when and how I want. 

I'm finally seeing the good things about the future...well about the end of the semester at least.  That's not right...I'm finally able to find joy in just the knowledge that in 4 weeks I'm done, where as last night and the past few days I've just been frustrated and stressed and unable to see anything past my frustrations and stesses.

I really like the JP kid from the Newman Center, he's so sweet and he may run for an office, I hope he does...we need new and faithful people at the Newman Center that aren't just there because they lack the social skills to have friends elsewhere.

I've had a few conversations with friends where they've told me that the end of this semester has left them too questioning who they really are.  If it's that they've put so many masks on they can't find who they are underneath or they feel out of place in their major, or location, or job, or something.  And I totally understand, not just sympathize or empathize, but I've been through it, I'm still going through it.  And half the time I don't know what to say or if I even have any words of comfort to give because I'm not comfortable period.

I've gotten rid of a lot of my masks I know I have, but I still hide so much from everyone.  And it's only when something bothers me incecently that anyone even notices that there's something off with me, and even if they notice, they have no clue what it's about. Sometimes when I name that mask, so to speak, and I figure out what it is that caused me to put it on or what causes me to keep it or what it does for my life, it's not easy to toss it.  I don't like what's underneath, it's vulnerable, it's something I want to hide obviously otherwise why would I have put the mask on in the first place.  But then I remind myself that unless I know who I really am I'm never going to be really happy, I'm never going to be able to truly give myself to anyone in service or love.  Often I don't even recognize what I find underneath, and often I just shove it back inside, but I'm trying.  I really do think that this summer is going to be a huge discovery for me.  I'm going to discover myself and Flagstaff and life I guess...

I do know that I'm supposed to be in Flagstaff, and I do know that I'm supposed to be a Social Worker and I do know I'm supposed to do something at the Newman Center before I leave Flag...so that stuff for me is figured out for me now I guess...it's just the other stuff.

Anyways, we have officer elections and a BBQ at the Newman Center on Thursday, I'll be there and I'll get a free dinner again which I don't mind.  I kinda really want to get people's thoughts and opinions though.  I want to know what they want from the Newman Center, what activities, what level of deepness in spirituality (what activities relating to that)...what will bring people in and give them what they're seeking?  I really want to do a lot of service projects, I also want to really get back to my faith.  I feel so out of it.  Like a weekly rosary or chaplet of divine mercy or bible study or faith sharing, or a combination of it all...If you have any thoughts let me know PLEASE, I'll beg if you want.  Even if you're not Catholic, what in your faith life works?

Well, this ended up being a lot longer than intended, if you made it through this congrats and I appologize for my rants and long-windedness ;P  But I do believe I'm off to bed or something...we'll see what happens. 

Goodnight everyone, good luck with the rest of your week (and semester) I hope you find time to relax and not stress, basically take a break...take a break for me if not for you :)  Anyway, y'all take care now ya hear, and call me if you need anything...I don't mind I promise!

So, last night I walked for probably a good 4 hours...I'm feeling good today.  However next time I'll definitely be wearing my knee brace.  I don't know haven't you ever just felt like getting out and walking?  I do, quite frequenlty, I usually don't just because like everyone last night got worried, it's not always that safe, but since I hurt my back I could either lie down flat or stand and I had way too much energy to be still.  I wasn't worried about my safety just so you all know, however everyone else was...I guess I appreciate it. But sometimes it makes me feel like nobody trusts me to take care of myself.  But I definitely got answers last night.  Nothing surprising, but it was about time for me, that I actually heart the answers.  It was one of those things.  I knew what God had told me, but I wanted it to not be true.  But it was, He's always right.  

On a different note: 
I've been ruminating the past few days on what Fr. Chauncey said on Sunday. Doubt is a choice, it's a choice to not believe in anything beyond yourself or your experiences.  Doubt is telling God that He either doesn't exist or that He has to prove Himself to us, individually.  Faith it taking others accounts of events and finding the truth in it...knowing and believing there's something beyond us and our experiences.  
However, God does show Himself to us, in little, sometime easy to over look ways every day.  It's up to us to pay attention and figure out the messages that He sends us. 

So, the right side of my back still hurts, including my arm.  It's kinda hard to move.  But it'll be okay I'm sure.  It doesn't hurt as bad as it did yesterday thats for sure.  But I think I need to stretch it out and just really relax.  If I still can't move well, I may just resign myself to asking someone for a massage. We'll see though...

Well that's it for now I guess...I hope you all have a good day, talk to you later :)

I feel like for a month I've seen nothing but clouds and rain or snow...the sun does not exist in my life right now it seems.  Even when I was in LA it was cloudy and rainy...could this be a metaphore for my life...that it is gray and dull and virtually no excitement except for the occational thunderstorm...perhaps.  Or that despite what goes on, it's just a cover, a mask of what is real, what is true.  Have I been masking myself again, pretending my life is something it isn't?  Even though I know there is something better and real, alive behind what I make it, I can't see it...so do I live it?  Is my life a joke...is everyone else laughing at me the same way I'm laughing at me...am I oblivious am I a joke, the joke?  Even now as I sit at the window and stare out towards the sky a piece of the clouds have broken to let in a sliver of light, it's a reminder of the truth...it shows the beauty of what is real...it sparkles it is pure, but it doesn't last...it will soon be gone and leave me in the gray, boring life that I lead, with little reminder of the life I want, but I will pretend that is the life I lead.
